## Reflection — Day 6 Session 1

- Lists store ordered changeable collections — use for data that updates
- Tuples store fixed unchangeable data — use for coordinates and constants
- Sets store unique values only — use to remove duplicates or compare groups
- Dictionaries store labelled data as key-value pairs — use for records
- List of dictionaries is the most important pattern — it is basically a table
- .append() adds to a list
- .remove() deletes from a list
- set() converts a list to unique values only
- .items() loops through both keys and values of a dictionary
- & intersection, | union, - difference are powerful set operations

